For sale is Kel-Tec’s flagship firearm - the RFB, the bullpup .308/7.62x51 rifle like no other.  This is the 18” barrel model and comes with an extra magazine and soft case.

TECHNICAL SPECS
Weight unloaded (no magazine):   8.1 lbs
Length:           26"
Barrel length:            18"

Practical range:         600m

The RFB is a short-stroke gas piston operated semi-automatic rifle in 7.62 mm NATO caliber. It accepts standard metric FAL type magazines which work "drop free" and do not need to be tilted in. Two 20 round magazines are included*. Barrels on current models are 18" long, with a chrome lined bore and chamber. The muzzle is threaded 5/8x24 TPI and comes equipped with our A2-style Flash Hider*. All controls are fully ambidextrous; the reciprocating operating handle can be switched to either side. The trigger mechanism is second to no other Bullpup ever built and better than nearly all commercial semi-auto rifles. The safety disconnects the trigger and blocks the hammer action. title: For Sale/Trade:  Howa M1500, Custom, Sub-MOA, Detach Magazine
postcontent:
Howa makes the action for the Sub-MOA Weatherby Vanguard rifles and was the barreled action for S&W's tactical Military/police rifles prior to S&W discontinuing the lines. This rifle is VERY accurate, short (for a long rifle), and built for accurate shooting inside 800m. I haven't pushed it further, but I am sure you can.

Facts:
20" Fluted Bull barrel and rail mount w/ Target crown from Howa, .308 Win, RoT is 1:10
Bell & Carlson Tactical Medalist Stock in Black, FREE FLOAT, full aluminum bedded
Original HOWA floorplate w/ internal box mag & release included
Legacy Sports removeable magazine floorplate with 2x 10rd magazines
Harris #9 (I think) flat bottom stock swivel adapter
Harris 6-9" bipod (non-swivel, non-notched model)
Uncle Mike's Sling swivels - 1"
"Horn Hunter" Gripper/ammo holding sling - not impressive, but functional

This rifle currently has a 4-16x50mm Millet TRS-1 optic on it. It's functional, illuminated, mil-dot, and works just fine for me. I can include it or keep it. Doesn't matter. 

The last/best 3 shot group I've shot with Hornady 150gr SST ammo in this rifle measured 0.214 from the centers @ 100yrds - Red's Indoor range South. It basically fits under a nickel. The trigger is extremely crisp and breaks as nicely as any rifle I have shot. The decelerator pad works great. The bolt action is smooth and commensurate with comparable weapons in that range.  YES, I've felt a $3000 rifle, and it is tighter and smoother. But if you can shoot, this rifle will hit the target.

Why sell it? I'm a lefty! I'm left eye dominant, and I've decided it is time to own that. My ARs have mostly been converted to fully Ambi. My 1911's got Ambi safeties. This rifle is one of the last Righty only set ups I have.

I'll trade, I'll sell, I'll do partial in betweens. I figure I have $1250 or so into this guy BEFORE to putting glass on it. I listed a price because I hate it when that is blank and that seems like a fair range. Make me an offer... Let's chat about it.

It is listed on TGT as well. $1000 for the rifle, $1300 OBO w/ the Millett TRS-1, and Millett Tactical rings.

title: For Sale:  PARA 1911 P14-45 LIMITED STAINLESS STEEL, 14 RD CAPACITY
postcontent:
This is the Limited which has all the factory extras like adjustable rear sights, Full Length Guide Rod, extended safety and controls, ramped/supported barrel etc.  This is the highly sought after "Made in Canada" model. These Para's are incredibly accurate and very reliable.  I’ve fired probably 500-750 rounds through it.  Every time I’ve ever taken it to the range people are amazed at its accuracy.  This gun is more accurate than you are.  I’ve fired Les Baer and Wilson Combat and I’d be comfortable putting this up against either at the range.
I bought this new in 2002, (before Para moved).  It does have some minimal wear marks.  I’m kind of picky and I notice some imperfections.  It sat on a gun rag in my nightstand until the kids got too old and it had to be locked away, and has since been stored in the original box in a climate controlled space.  Function is flawless.  In all the rounds I’ve fired I had one jam from a failure to eject on local range reloads when it was being broken in.  Cause was probably dirt from reloads, never had an issue since.  Gun has been cleaned and oiled after each visit to the range and periodically regardless as part of standard maintenance.  I generally take it to the range at least once a year and fire off a mag or two just because it’s so sweet to fire.
Included are:
Para P14.45 Limited in Stainless (duh)
Factory 10rd Mag
After Market Hi-Cap mag
Original box, paperwork and 1911 tool.
I’m asking for $750 which I think is a fair price.  Looking for a no nonsense deal and a buyer with cash and an Ohio Driver’s License per private exchange guidlines.  Will meet in a mutually agreeable place.  If questions, offers, etc. please ask.  Reasonable requests will be responded to ASAP.
